text: - Hey.
Louie Duck here.

And today, I'm counting down
some of my favorite treasures.

Wait.
Am I being paid to do this?
PRODUCER: Nope!

Starting my list
at number four is
the golden khopesh of Toth-Ra.

Ooh.
Why?
It's made of gold.
Let's see how I found it.

Number three on my
list of top treasures

is the skull of
the Yukon mammoth.

While it may look terrifying,
this thing actually

helped lead Uncle Scrooge
to one of the greatest

treasures of all time, so
totally worth the creep factor.
You know, that felt good.

I should definitely
be paid for this one.
PRODUCER: Nope!

Up next, number two on my
countdown of top treasures
is Lena's diamond dagger.
I mean, hello!
It's a dagger made of diamonds.

Just think how
much you could get
for that on the utensil market.

But Lena had something
else in mind.

And finally, number one on my
top treasure countdown is--
drum roll please.

[record scratch]
What?
No drum roll?

PRODUCER: No!
- Seriously?
Fine.

Look, my number one
is the found lamp.

A gold lamp that
can grant wishes?
Ha, count me in.

Thanks for watching
my "DuckTales"
top treasure countdown.

If you enjoyed this list,
please send cash or money order

to the mansion on Killmotor
Hill, Duckberg, Calisota,

and make out any checks to
Llewellyn Duck, care of--
PRODUCER: Louie!
No one is sending you money!
LOUIE DUCK: Fine!
